{{- /*
fingerprint.tmpl — comment-only dependency fingerprint block for run_onchange_
scripts (the canonical form of the script-prefix policy in AGENTS.md).

Emits one `#   <path>  <sha256>` line per file matched by each glob pattern.
chezmoi hashes the whole rendered script to decide whether to re-run it, so a
changed dependency changes the rendered content and re-triggers the script.

`include . | sha256sum` hashes file CONTENT (a bare `sha256sum .` would hash
the path STRING); the `(stat .).isDir` guard skips the directories a `**`
glob matches. For a `.tmpl` dependency this hashes the raw template text
(its onepasswordRead refs, not resolved secrets), so no secret ever enters
the fingerprint.

Usage (from any script template):

  {{ includeTemplate "fingerprint.tmpl" (dict
       "sourceDir" .chezmoi.sourceDir
       "globs" (list "system/linux/etc/**" ".chezmoidata/fonts.yaml")) }}
*/ -}}
{{- $sourceDir := .sourceDir -}}
{{- range $pattern := .globs -}}
{{- range glob (joinPath $sourceDir $pattern) -}}
{{- if not (stat .).isDir }}
#   {{ . | trimPrefix $sourceDir | trimPrefix "/" }}  {{ include . | sha256sum }}
{{- end -}}
{{- end -}}
{{- end }}
